[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":773},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F03\u002F13\u002Fconsole-debugging-tools\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F03\u002F13\u002Fconsole-debugging-tools\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F03\u002F13\u002Fconsole-debugging-tools\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F03\u002F13\u002Fconsole-debugging-tools\u002F":748,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F03\u002F13\u002Fconsole-debugging-tools\u002F":757},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20200313\u002F3743352418\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":732,"date":733,"description":734,"extension":735,"lang":736,"meta":737,"navigation":738,"path":739,"readingMinutes":740,"seo":741,"standalone":742,"stem":743,"tags":744,"tldr":745,"updated":733,"url":746,"__hash__":747},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fconsole-debugging-tools.md","Console Is the Debug Tool You Already Have — Here's How to Actually Use It","1001544208",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":720},"minimark",[11,16,28,31,45,51,55,61,110,113,117,122,166,173,180,183,186,247,253,257,274,327,333,378,384,395,399,410,516,519,525,528,616,619,624,642,646,649,668,672,675,694,698,701,705,716],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24,25,27],"p",{},"When you're writing JavaScript, you end up using ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"console"," to debug all the time. So this post takes a quick look at ",[21,26,23],{},".",[12,29,30],{"id":23},"Console",[17,32,33,34,37,38,41,42,44],{},"Way back, some people debugged with ",[21,35,36],{},"window.alert()",". Honestly that's a pretty bad way to do it — every single time, the ",[21,39,40],{},"alert"," popup blocks you. And if you're trying to watch something that fires repeatedly, like a listener, it's even worse, because you'll get a flood of ",[21,43,40],{}," windows.",[17,46,47,48,50],{},"One thing to keep in mind: different browsers render these a little differently. So here I'm only listing the ",[21,49,23],{}," methods I've personally used and found handy. Everything below was tested on Chrome 80.",[12,52,54],{"id":53},"consolelog","console.log",[17,56,57,58,60],{},"The most common debug line is ",[21,59,54],{},". Most beginners reach for this one, and it's about as easy as it gets.",[62,63,68],"pre",{"className":64,"code":65,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","var a = 1;\nconsole.log(a); \u002F\u002F 1\n","js","",[21,69,70,93],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,72,75,79,83,86,90],"span",{"class":73,"line":74},"line",1,[71,76,78],{"class":77},"sOudu","var",[71,80,82],{"class":81},"s8XSl"," a ",[71,84,85],{"class":77},"=",[71,87,89],{"class":88},"stw71"," 1",[71,91,92],{"class":81},";\n",[71,94,96,99,103,106],{"class":73,"line":95},2,[71,97,98],{"class":81},"console.",[71,100,102],{"class":101},"scAaK","log",[71,104,105],{"class":81},"(a); ",[71,107,109],{"class":108},"sGBqm","\u002F\u002F 1\n",[17,111,112],{},"It's so common that I won't say much more about it.",[12,114,116],{"id":115},"consoletable","console.table",[17,118,119,121],{},[21,120,116],{}," is great for looking at arrays or objects. For example:",[62,123,125],{"className":64,"code":124,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"var a = ['1', 'B', 'c'];\nconsole.table(a);\n",[21,126,127,156],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,128,129,131,133,135,138,142,145,148,150,153],{"class":73,"line":74},[71,130,78],{"class":77},[71,132,82],{"class":81},[71,134,85],{"class":77},[71,136,137],{"class":81}," [",[71,139,141],{"class":140},"sWayO","'1'",[71,143,144],{"class":81},", ",[71,146,147],{"class":140},"'B'",[71,149,144],{"class":81},[71,151,152],{"class":140},"'c'",[71,154,155],{"class":81},"];\n",[71,157,158,160,163],{"class":73,"line":95},[71,159,98],{"class":81},[71,161,162],{"class":101},"table",[71,164,165],{"class":81},"(a);\n",[17,167,168,169,172],{},"It renders kind of like an HTML table, which makes it easier to read, and you can see the ",[21,170,171],{},"index"," at a glance.",[17,174,175],{},[176,177],"img",{"alt":178,"src":179},"console.table rendering an array","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-03-13%2011.06.57.png",[17,181,182],{},"You can even click a column header to sort. Really nice tool for inspecting arrays.",[17,184,185],{},"Objects come out the same way.",[62,187,189],{"className":64,"code":188,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"var a = {\n  a: '1',\n  b: 'B',\n  c: 'c',\n}\nconsole.table(a);\n",[21,190,191,202,212,222,232,238],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,192,193,195,197,199],{"class":73,"line":74},[71,194,78],{"class":77},[71,196,82],{"class":81},[71,198,85],{"class":77},[71,200,201],{"class":81}," {\n",[71,203,204,207,209],{"class":73,"line":95},[71,205,206],{"class":81},"  a: ",[71,208,141],{"class":140},[71,210,211],{"class":81},",\n",[71,213,215,218,220],{"class":73,"line":214},3,[71,216,217],{"class":81},"  b: ",[71,219,147],{"class":140},[71,221,211],{"class":81},[71,223,225,228,230],{"class":73,"line":224},4,[71,226,227],{"class":81},"  c: ",[71,229,152],{"class":140},[71,231,211],{"class":81},[71,233,235],{"class":73,"line":234},5,[71,236,237],{"class":81},"}\n",[71,239,241,243,245],{"class":73,"line":240},6,[71,242,98],{"class":81},[71,244,162],{"class":101},[71,246,165],{"class":81},[17,248,249],{},[176,250],{"alt":251,"src":252},"console.table rendering an object","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-03-13%2013.13.24.png",[12,254,256],{"id":255},"consoledir","console.dir",[17,258,259,260,263,264,267,268,270,271,273],{},"Think of ",[21,261,262],{},"console.dir()"," as a souped-up ",[21,265,266],{},"console.log()",". When you use ",[21,269,266],{}," to inspect something, you often also want to see its properties — but ",[21,272,266],{}," won't show those. For example:",[62,275,277],{"className":64,"code":276,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"var a = function() {\n  console.log('log');\n};\nconsole.log(a); \u002F\u002F you only see the function\n",[21,278,279,295,311,316],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,280,281,283,286,289,292],{"class":73,"line":74},[71,282,78],{"class":77},[71,284,285],{"class":101}," a",[71,287,288],{"class":77}," =",[71,290,291],{"class":77}," function",[71,293,294],{"class":81},"() {\n",[71,296,297,300,302,305,308],{"class":73,"line":95},[71,298,299],{"class":81},"  console.",[71,301,102],{"class":101},[71,303,304],{"class":81},"(",[71,306,307],{"class":140},"'log'",[71,309,310],{"class":81},");\n",[71,312,313],{"class":73,"line":214},[71,314,315],{"class":81},"};\n",[71,317,318,320,322,324],{"class":73,"line":224},[71,319,98],{"class":81},[71,321,102],{"class":101},[71,323,105],{"class":81},[71,325,326],{"class":108},"\u002F\u002F you only see the function\n",[17,328,329,330,332],{},"When you want the finer details, use ",[21,331,262],{},". It gives you a little arrow you can click to expand.",[62,334,336],{"className":64,"code":335,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"var a = function() {\n  console.log('log');\n};\nconsole.dir(a); \u002F\u002F you get the finer details — proto, name, and so on\n",[21,337,338,350,362,366],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,339,340,342,344,346,348],{"class":73,"line":74},[71,341,78],{"class":77},[71,343,285],{"class":101},[71,345,288],{"class":77},[71,347,291],{"class":77},[71,349,294],{"class":81},[71,351,352,354,356,358,360],{"class":73,"line":95},[71,353,299],{"class":81},[71,355,102],{"class":101},[71,357,304],{"class":81},[71,359,307],{"class":140},[71,361,310],{"class":81},[71,363,364],{"class":73,"line":214},[71,365,315],{"class":81},[71,367,368,370,373,375],{"class":73,"line":224},[71,369,98],{"class":81},[71,371,372],{"class":101},"dir",[71,374,105],{"class":81},[71,376,377],{"class":108},"\u002F\u002F you get the finer details — proto, name, and so on\n",[17,379,380],{},[176,381],{"alt":382,"src":383},"console.log vs console.dir","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-03-13%2011.19.28.png",[17,385,386,387,394],{},"One thing though — this method isn't part of the standard, and you can see that noted right at the top of the ",[388,389,393],"a",{"href":390,"rel":391},"https:\u002F\u002Fdeveloper.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Fdocs\u002FWeb\u002FAPI\u002Fconsole\u002Fdir_static",[392],"nofollow","MDN"," docs.",[12,396,398],{"id":397},"consoletime-consoletimeend","console.time && console.timeEnd",[17,400,401,402,405,406,409],{},"These two are pretty special. With ",[21,403,404],{},"console.time"," and ",[21,407,408],{},"console.timeEnd"," you can measure how long a chunk of code takes to run. Say you've got this:",[62,411,413],{"className":64,"code":412,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"console.time('start timer');\nfor(var i = 0; i \u003C= 9999; i++) {\n  if (i === 9999) {\n    console.log('done.');\n  }\n}\nconsole.timeEnd('start timer');\n",[21,414,415,429,464,479,493,498,502],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,416,417,419,422,424,427],{"class":73,"line":74},[71,418,98],{"class":81},[71,420,421],{"class":101},"time",[71,423,304],{"class":81},[71,425,426],{"class":140},"'start timer'",[71,428,310],{"class":81},[71,430,431,434,436,438,441,443,446,449,452,455,458,461],{"class":73,"line":95},[71,432,433],{"class":77},"for",[71,435,304],{"class":81},[71,437,78],{"class":77},[71,439,440],{"class":81}," i ",[71,442,85],{"class":77},[71,444,445],{"class":88}," 0",[71,447,448],{"class":81},"; i ",[71,450,451],{"class":77},"\u003C=",[71,453,454],{"class":88}," 9999",[71,456,457],{"class":81},"; i",[71,459,460],{"class":77},"++",[71,462,463],{"class":81},") {\n",[71,465,466,469,472,475,477],{"class":73,"line":214},[71,467,468],{"class":77},"  if",[71,470,471],{"class":81}," (i ",[71,473,474],{"class":77},"===",[71,476,454],{"class":88},[71,478,463],{"class":81},[71,480,481,484,486,488,491],{"class":73,"line":224},[71,482,483],{"class":81},"    console.",[71,485,102],{"class":101},[71,487,304],{"class":81},[71,489,490],{"class":140},"'done.'",[71,492,310],{"class":81},[71,494,495],{"class":73,"line":234},[71,496,497],{"class":81},"  }\n",[71,499,500],{"class":73,"line":240},[71,501,237],{"class":81},[71,503,505,507,510,512,514],{"class":73,"line":504},7,[71,506,98],{"class":81},[71,508,509],{"class":101},"timeEnd",[71,511,304],{"class":81},[71,513,426],{"class":140},[71,515,310],{"class":81},[17,517,518],{},"This one runs in about 0.5 ms.",[17,520,521],{},[176,522],{"alt":523,"src":524},"execution time","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-03-13%2011.33.56.png",[17,526,527],{},"But what about this?",[62,529,531],{"className":64,"code":530,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"console.time('start timer');\nfor(var i = 0; i \u003C= 9999; i++) {\n  if (i \u003C 9999) {\n    console.log('done.');\n  }\n}\nconsole.timeEnd('start timer');\n",[21,532,533,545,571,584,596,600,604],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,534,535,537,539,541,543],{"class":73,"line":74},[71,536,98],{"class":81},[71,538,421],{"class":101},[71,540,304],{"class":81},[71,542,426],{"class":140},[71,544,310],{"class":81},[71,546,547,549,551,553,555,557,559,561,563,565,567,569],{"class":73,"line":95},[71,548,433],{"class":77},[71,550,304],{"class":81},[71,552,78],{"class":77},[71,554,440],{"class":81},[71,556,85],{"class":77},[71,558,445],{"class":88},[71,560,448],{"class":81},[71,562,451],{"class":77},[71,564,454],{"class":88},[71,566,457],{"class":81},[71,568,460],{"class":77},[71,570,463],{"class":81},[71,572,573,575,577,580,582],{"class":73,"line":214},[71,574,468],{"class":77},[71,576,471],{"class":81},[71,578,579],{"class":77},"\u003C",[71,581,454],{"class":88},[71,583,463],{"class":81},[71,585,586,588,590,592,594],{"class":73,"line":224},[71,587,483],{"class":81},[71,589,102],{"class":101},[71,591,304],{"class":81},[71,593,490],{"class":140},[71,595,310],{"class":81},[71,597,598],{"class":73,"line":234},[71,599,497],{"class":81},[71,601,602],{"class":73,"line":240},[71,603,237],{"class":81},[71,605,606,608,610,612,614],{"class":73,"line":504},[71,607,98],{"class":81},[71,609,509],{"class":101},[71,611,304],{"class":81},[71,613,426],{"class":140},[71,615,310],{"class":81},[17,617,618],{},"You'll find it takes 481 ms to finish (the exact number depends on your machine).",[17,620,621],{},[176,622],{"alt":523,"src":623},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202020-03-13%2011.35.51.png",[17,625,626,627,630,631,634,635,638,639,27],{},"The thing to watch here: ",[21,628,629],{},"console.time(name)"," needs a name passed in, and the ",[21,632,633],{},"name"," you give ",[21,636,637],{},"console.timeEnd(name)"," has to match the one you used in ",[21,640,641],{},"console.time()",[12,643,645],{"id":644},"consolewarn","console.warn",[17,647,648],{},"Those yellow warning messages you often see in the console? That's this method.",[62,650,652],{"className":64,"code":651,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"console.warn('yellow warning message');\n",[21,653,654],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,655,656,658,661,663,666],{"class":73,"line":74},[71,657,98],{"class":81},[71,659,660],{"class":101},"warn",[71,662,304],{"class":81},[71,664,665],{"class":140},"'yellow warning message'",[71,667,310],{"class":81},[12,669,671],{"id":670},"consoleerror","console.error",[17,673,674],{},"And if there's a yellow warning, there's definitely a red one too — the more serious-looking error.",[62,676,678],{"className":64,"code":677,"language":66,"meta":67,"style":67},"console.error('red error message');\n",[21,679,680],{"__ignoreMap":67},[71,681,682,684,687,689,692],{"class":73,"line":74},[71,683,98],{"class":81},[71,685,686],{"class":101},"error",[71,688,304],{"class":81},[71,690,691],{"class":140},"'red error message'",[71,693,310],{"class":81},[12,695,697],{"id":696},"consoleclear","console.clear",[17,699,700],{},"This one's simpler. It clears the console and outputs \"Console was cleared\". Give it a try yourself.",[12,702,704],{"id":703},"references","References",[706,707,708],"ul",{},[709,710,711],"li",{},[388,712,715],{"href":713,"rel":714},"https:\u002F\u002Fdeveloper.mozilla.org\u002Fen-US\u002Fdocs\u002FWeb\u002FAPI\u002Fconsole",[392],"MDN Console",[717,718,719],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sOudu, html code.shiki .sOudu{--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-default:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .s8XSl, html code.shiki .s8XSl{--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-default:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .stw71, html code.shiki .stw71{--shiki-light:#005CC5;--shiki-default:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .scAaK, html code.shiki .scAaK{--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sGBqm, html code.shiki .sGBqm{--shiki-light:#6A737D;--shiki-default:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#BDC4CC}html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .dark .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-dark);background: var(--shiki-dark-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-dark-font-style);font-weight: var(--